                    "ctaUrl": {
                      "value": "/rolex-mentor-protege/recent-mentorships/visual-arts/carrie-mae-weems-and-camila-rodriguez-triana"
                    },
                    "descriptionText": {
                      "value": "Part of Camila Rodríguez Triana’s appeal as a protégée for Carrie Mae Weems was that she came from a different country and another world, yet their work is bound by ties of similarity. Both explore the impact of colonialism, displacement, identity and belonging, both have a strand of memory and remembrance in the pieces they make. Weems admires Triana’s act of “making”: she uses stitching and textiles to express her ideas about Colombia’s violent past and its struggle into a different future.\n\n"
                    },
                    "descriptionTitle": {
                      "value": ""
                    },
                    "imageLandscape_src": {
